section.p:
When  renders documents, it causes the browser to consume more
        memory than the original document size. To work with large documents, you can configure  to fold some of the elements by default. To do this, you need to
        create a custom CSS file that specifies the folding (for example, specifying that all the
        sections are folded by
        default):section{
    -oxy-foldable:true;
    -oxy-folded: true;
    -oxy-not-foldable-child: title;
}
